The formula for speed is:

\[v=\frac{distance}{time}

The formula for velocity is:

\[v=\frac{distance}{time} \times \frac{change in direction}{change in time}

In words, speed is a measurement of how far an object travels in a given amount of time, while velocity is a measurement of how far an object travels in a given amount of time, and in which direction.
